chemlambda demos

    Watch the appearance of a "walker". Technically this is pred(28)=27, from lambda calculus, but done in chemlambda. The walker led to the discovery of chemlambda quines.
    You can see many short animations in the chemlambda collection.
    This demo is done by using the script moving_random_metabo.sh and the file bigpred.mol from the gh-pages branch of the repo. Remark that it is the same script as in the first battle of microbes.
    Because random, each execution is different. See another one on youtube.
